==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French [[cocodrille]] (modern [[#French|crocodile]]), from mediaeval Latin [[cocodrillus]], from Latin [[cocodrilus]], from Greek [[κροκόδιλος]].  The word was later refashioned after the Latin and Greek forms.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈkrɒkədaɪl/}} (''UK'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any of a variety of related [[predatory]] [[amphibious]] [[reptiles]], related to the [[alligator]].
# A long line or procession of people (especially children) walking together.

====Related terms====
*[[crocodile tears]]

